reviewText: My 6 and 2 year old daughters love this movie! They sing along to the songs. Great for a car ride or road trip.

Pretty standard Dora, I wish the actual ice skating story was longer because my four year old doesn't really like the Shape Train one but really liked the "ice witch one". We rented this and although we own a lot of the Dora movies I probably won't purchase the full length film. She much prefers Dora's Knighthood Adventure or Dora Saves the Crystal Kingdom.

My girls love Dora the Explorer. This DVD contains three episodes from the Nick Jr. cartoon. Amazon doesn't always do a good job on their DVD episode listings so here are the episodes that are included on this DVD:

1. Dora's Ice Skating Spectacular - Dora and Boots must help their Snow friends get their ice skates back.
2. Catch that Shape Train - Dora and Boots must find a runaway train's steering wheel.
3. Dora and Perrito to the Rescue - Dora and her dog must save Boots from the Big River.
My daughter loves Dora and loves this cartoon. Next thing to do is buy her a digital copy.

I was a little disappointed in this video.  I was expecting the full dvd to be the Ice Skating Spectacular but there was only 1 short episode then the rest of the video was just regular Dora episodes.  I don't think I will be renting any of the other Dora DVDs.  My granddaughter liked it but she would have been just as satisfied with the previous seasons that I could have streamed for free with my Amazon Prime.

My four year old loves this episode and is engaged throughout the entire length.  It promotes friendship and being nice to others as well as having confidence in yourself and your abilities
I selected this from the movie category and expected a Dora movie about skating.  It was three random TV episodes packaged together complete with three theme songs and three sets of credits.
My granddaughter  loves this movie, she loves it and sings all the songs over and over.  Dora is always a big hit at our house.

MY GRANDDAUGHTER REALLY LIKED THIS MOVIE AND LOOKING FORWARD TO MORE LIKE THIS.  SHE IS GETTING SKATES AND WE WANTED HER TO SEE HER DORA SKATING SO THAT MOTIVATES HER MORE.  I RECOMMEND TO ANY CHILD THAT LOVES DORA THANK YOU

In my opinion the Dora videos/stories are appropriate for children in preschool.  We don't allow our 3 1/2 year old much screen time, but when we do, we like that the Dora videos depict positive situations and they combine English and Spanish.
Your children will be entertained if they are Dora fans. Nice movie for little ice skating fans. I gave it 4 stars because it's not one of those movies children will want to watch repeatedly.

My granddaughter is taking Spanish at school and she knew all the Spanish words, and shapes and got bored with the DVD very quickly, it was not a product she could learn from and keep her attention. Sorry!
My two year old daughter absolutely loves Dora!  This is by far her most favorite one yet!  Highley recommend it!

My little girl loves Dora, so it was no surprise that she loves this movie!  She loved it so much, actually, that she bought it on my Kindle without asking, lol.  Needless to say, I turned on parental controls =)

We bought this solely to entertain on a long car trip but now watch it or re-enact it daily. Hourly. This is some toddler version of the Mona Lisa crossed with Citizen Kane and possibly crack. Hug tight and turn!
My 3 year old said 5 stars! I say that too! 3 great episodes endless excitement for all Dora fans!
I think it was fine I bought it as a gift for my niece and she seemed thrilled. Will keep! SUPER fast shipping.
My granddaughter loves everything Dora. She watch this at least three times on the day of purchase and several more times since then.
We love Dora and this is another delightful show. The children love the new songs in this one. If your child likes Dora Saves the Snow Princess movie, this one is similar.

I had got this for my 2 1/2 year old daughter for Christmas and all she been wanting is to watch this in her new Dora chair...... now we don't have to wait year after year for this to come on tv every year..

We spent over $50 on amazon movies/videos hoping to download them so the girls can watch them on the tv and in the car... Guess you can only stream them!?!! We have limited data, Satellite internet, and streaming them will only work for part of the month till we hit our cap. What a waste.

A real disappointment for my toddlers. We all anticipated a movie-length show about Dora iceskating. Instead, it's just 3 random episodes. I think they'll available free via Prime video so the rental was a waste of money and a real let-down.
In general it's real Dumb Dora, my kids will watch it.  But, please there are so many better things to watch with your kids. Find one, this is not it.
